## Utility Classes
- Use Tailwind utility classes instead of custom CSS when possible
- Group utilities logically: layout → spacing → typography → colors → effects
- Use responsive prefixes: `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:` for mobile-first design

## Custom Colors
- Follow [design-system.mdc](.cursor/rules/design-system.mdc) for color palette, especially the **primary group** (`--color-primary` and variations)
- Define custom colors in `app/globals.css` using CSS variables
- Map CSS variables to Tailwind theme in `@theme inline` block
- Use only design system tokens `--color-*` / Tailwind classes (`bg-primary`, `text-primary`, `border-primary`, etc.); avoid loose hex values
- The primary group must be centralized to facilitate constant changes
- Color tokens matching Oaureal design system:
  - `bg` / `text-bg`: `#000000` (black background — mandatory base)
  - `primary` / `text-primary` / `border-primary`: Celeste neónsito (`--color-primary`) — important landing color
  - `primary-light` / `primary-dark`: Variations for hovers, glows, active states
  - `text` / `text-muted`: White (#FFFFFF) and light gray (#E0E0E0) for readability on black
  - `secondary` (optional): Only if a second neon color is needed

## Class Organization
- Sort classes by: layout → spacing → typography → colors → effects
- Use `cn()` utility from `@/lib/utils` for conditional classes
- Avoid arbitrary values `[custom-value]` when a utility class exists
- Group related utilities together for readability

```typescript
// ✅ Good
<div className="flex items-center gap-4 p-6 bg-black text-white rounded-xl">
  <span className="text-[#a5f0fa] font-bold">Oaureal</span>
</div>

// ❌ Bad
<div className="bg-black text-white flex items-center gap-4 p-6 rounded-xl">
```

## Component Patterns
- Extract repeated patterns into reusable components in `components/ui/`
- Use Tailwind's component classes for consistent styling
- Leverage Tailwind's spacing scale: `p-4`, `gap-6`, `mb-8`
- Use consistent border radius: `rounded-xl`, `rounded-2xl`, `rounded-3xl`

## Performance
- Avoid over-nesting utility classes
- Use Tailwind's purge/content configuration automatically via v4
- Prefer Tailwind utilities over inline styles
- Use `@apply` sparingly, only for repeated patterns

## Dark Mode
- Oaureal uses dark theme by default
- All components should work with dark background (`bg-black`, `bg-[#050505]`)
- Use high contrast text colors for readability
- Test color combinations for accessibility

## Oaureal-Specific Patterns

### Color Usage
- Primary blue (`#011797`): Main brand color, used for gradients and accents
- Secondary purple (`#54008c`): Secondary brand color, used in gradients
- Accent cyan (`#a5f0fa`): Highlights, CTAs, interactive elements
- Black backgrounds: `bg-black`, `bg-[#050505]` for depth variation

### Typography
- Follow [design-system.mdc](.cursor/rules/design-system.mdc) for typography roles
- Replace generic "font-serif / font-mono" with design system roles: `font-logo`, `font-title`, `font-subtitle`, `font-body`
- Use `font-logo` (Cormorant/Lora) for brand logo
- Use `font-title` (Michroma) for headings, H1, H2, banners
- Use `font-subtitle` (Exo 2/Nunito) for CTAs, labels, secondary text
- Use `font-body` (Roboto) for paragraphs, descriptions, blog content
- Use `tracking-[0.3em]` for spaced-out uppercase text when needed
- Use `italic` for emphasis in headings when appropriate

### Spacing & Layout
- Use consistent padding: `p-6`, `p-8`, `p-10` for sections
- Use `max-w-6xl` or `max-w-4xl` for content containers
- Use `gap-6`, `gap-8`, `gap-10` for grid/flex spacing
- Use `py-24` for section vertical padding

### Effects & Animations
- Use `backdrop-blur-md` or `backdrop-blur-xl` for glassmorphism when needed
- Use `border-white/5` or `border-white/10` for subtle borders
- Use `bg-white/5` or `bg-white/10` for subtle overlays
- Use shadow utilities with primary color: `shadow-[0_0_20px_var(--color-primary)]` or `shadow-primary` for glow effects
- Gradients and glow only on titles (Michroma), CTA buttons, or key elements
- Avoid saturation; the celeste neon glow on black is the desired effect

### Responsive Design
- Mobile-first approach: base styles for mobile, then `md:`, `lg:` breakpoints
- Hide/show elements: `hidden md:flex` for responsive navigation
- Adjust text sizes: `text-5xl md:text-8xl` for responsive typography
- Grid layouts: `grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3` for responsive grids
